{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":3130210,"name":"Saaleh","username":"Sallyboy","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/sallyboy/{size}/195469_2.png","created_at":"2023-01-20T01:12:57.771Z","cooked":"

Hello, I am a programmer on Team 4500, and we have recently came across many issues with our swerve. Many fixes have been made to it since, and the problem has been narrowed down to a problem with the NavX. I have attached an image of the error.

We have tried changing the “port” from IC2.Port.kMXP to SPI.Port.kMXP. We have also used SSH to get into the rio, and have clarified that there is no “vmxHaljni” file, only “wpijni.so”. I wonder if this could be the root of the issue?

IMG_04351920×1440 319 KB

Peter_Johnson:

I’ve heard a couple of reports that this is an issue with either 2023.0.2 or 2023.0.3… try downgrading/upgrading the navx vendor dep.

Yes, there was an issue with 2023.0.2. 2023.0.3 fixed the issue. Based on the error messages, upgrading will solve the issue.

Also make sure you are running the right Vendor JSON. They changed it. It used to be…
https://www.kauailabs.com/dist/frc/2022/navx_frc.json

Now it is…
https://dev.studica.com/releases/2023/NavX.json

This was our issue. As of writing this, they finally fixed it on their web site. There is also new firmware for the NavX.
